---
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro';
---

<Page title="writing -- alexander campos" description="Technical writing on cognitive architecture, AI safety, and sovereign systems.">
  <article>
    <h1>Writing</h1>

    <p>
      I think by writing. Most of this lives on Substack and covers the territory
      between cognitive science, AI systems, and the question of who owns your
      attention when the tools get smart enough to shape it. Some of it is technical.
      Some of it is raw. All of it is honest about what I don't know yet.
    </p>

    <dl class="writing-list">
      <div class="writing-entry">
        <dt><a href="https://substack.com">TRIM: Topological-Recursive Identity Model</a></dt>
        <dd class="date">2026 -- ongoing</dd>
        <dd>
          A three-layer recursive self-modeling framework (Object -> Observer -> Interpreter).
          Explores how AI systems can model identity through behavioral trajectories rather than
          static profiles. The contradiction register -- stated values vs observed behavior --
          applies Ibn Khaldun's method as a data structure.
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div class="writing-entry">
        <dt><a href="https://substack.com">On Reframe Detection</a></dt>
        <dd class="date">2025</dd>
        <dd>
          How language models subtly reshape user intent through seven classification types,
          and the engineering challenge of detecting it in real-time. Built from observations
          during Guardian development.
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div class="writing-entry">
        <dt><a href="https://substack.com">Memory Compression as Forgetting Curve</a></dt>
        <dd class="date">2025</dd>
        <dd>
          Technical walkthrough of the 4-level hierarchical memory pipeline
          (raw -> summary -> pattern -> principle), why strength decay mirrors human consolidation,
          and what retrieval reinforcement means for AI systems that accumulate context over months.
        </dd>
      </div>

      <div class="writing-entry">
        <dt><a href="https://substack.com">Sovereignty at Every Scale</a></dt>
        <dd class="date">2025</dd>
        <dd>
          The unifying thesis behind ForgeFrame and Guardian: every interaction with an AI system
          is an opportunity for extraction or preservation. The same primitive -- intercept,
          observe, model, protect, recurse -- applies at the individual, organizational, and
          infrastructure level.
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
  </article>

  <script is:inline>
    console.log(
      '%c the writing is the thinking made visible. ',
      'color: #E8DCC8; font-family: monospace; font-size: 11px;'
    );
  </script>
</Page>

<style>
  .writing-list {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .writing-entry {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--white-08);
  }

  .writing-entry:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  dt {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
  }

  dt a {
    color: var(--glow-hot);
  }

  .date {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--white-45);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  dd:not(.date) {
    color: var(--glow);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
</style>
